<title type="html"><![CDATA[Emulating Pro Am Racing (MMC1)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6341&amp;p=60674#p60674"><![CDATA[
It turns off the screen half way through, uses Sprite DMA from ROM to clear the sprite table, then writes some new sprites using the PPU registers, and no DMA.<br /><br />The MMC1 version is more sane, it just changes the nametable and scrolls.  Nothing crazy.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Fri Apr 30, 2010 2:12 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
